# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- Withdrawal Requests
- Withdrawal Validation
- Balance Reservation
- Withdrawal Approval
- Withdrawal Rejection
- Withdrawal History
- Financial Audit Trail

This module handles real money leaving the platform.

---

# Core Flow

User

↓

Available Balance

↓

Create Withdrawal Request

↓

Pending

↓

Admin Review

↓

Approved

OR

Rejected

↓

Bank Transfer

↓

Completed

---

# Source Of Truth

WithdrawRequest table is the source of truth.

Do not calculate withdrawal history from transactions.

Persist every withdrawal request.

Never delete withdrawal records.

---

# WithdrawRequest Entity

Suggested fields:

- Id
- UserId
- Amount
- BankName
- BankAccountNumber
- BankAccountHolder
- Status
- RequestedAt
- ApprovedAt
- RejectedAt
- CompletedAt
- RejectionReason
- CreatedAt
- UpdatedAt

---

# Withdrawal Status Rules

Use enums from:

docs/enums.md

Allowed:

Pending

Approved

Rejected

Completed

---

Lifecycle

Pending

↓

Approved

↓

Completed

---

Pending

↓

Rejected

---

Forbidden

Completed

↓

Pending

---

Rejected

↓

Approved

---

Completed

↓

Rejected

---

Status transitions must be explicit.

---

# Balance Validation Rules

Before creating withdrawal:

Validate:

AvailableBalance >= Amount

---

Reject:

Amount > Balance

Amount <= 0

---

Example

Balance

100,000

Withdrawal

120,000

↓

Fail

---

# Minimum Withdrawal Rules

Configurable.

Example:

```text
50,000 VND
```

Must come from configuration.

Never hardcode.

---

# Maximum Withdrawal Rules

Configurable.

Example:

```text
5,000,000 VND
```

Must come from configuration.

---

# Available Balance Rules

Withdrawal uses:

AvailableBalance

Never use:

PendingBalance

EstimatedBalance

Pending commissions cannot be withdrawn.

---

# Balance Reservation Rules

Recommended MVP Strategy

Immediately deduct balance when request created.

Example

Balance

100,000

↓

Withdrawal

80,000

↓

Available Balance

20,000

---

Purpose:

Prevent double spending.

---

# Rejection Rules

If withdrawal rejected:

Restore balance.

Example

Available Balance

20,000

↓

Rejected

↓

Available Balance

100,000

---

Must create audit transaction.

---

# Completion Rules

Completed means:

Money has been transferred.

Only Admin may mark as Completed.

---

# Financial Transaction Rules

Every withdrawal action must create transaction records.

Suggested transaction types:

WithdrawalRequested

WithdrawalRejected

WithdrawalCompleted

BalanceAdjustment

---

Purpose:

Audit

Dispute resolution

Financial history

---

# Bank Information Rules

Required:

BankName

BankAccountNumber

BankAccountHolder

---

Validation:

Non-empty

Length limits

Basic format validation

---

Do not validate against bank APIs in MVP.

---

# Withdrawal Ownership Rules

Withdrawal belongs to:

Authenticated User

---

User may:

Create withdrawal

View own withdrawals

---

User may NOT:

Approve withdrawal

Reject withdrawal

Complete withdrawal

---

# Admin Rules

Admin may:

View all withdrawals

Approve withdrawal

Reject withdrawal

Complete withdrawal

---

Admin actions must be logged.

---

# Duplicate Withdrawal Rules

Multiple withdrawals allowed.

Provided:

Sufficient balance exists.

---

Do not block users from creating multiple requests.

Balance validation handles risk.

---

# Idempotency Rules

Critical Requirement

Approval processing must be idempotent.

---

Example

Approve Request

↓

Network Retry

↓

No duplicate processing

---

Balance must never be deducted twice.

---

# Audit Trail Rules

Store:

CreatedBy

ApprovedBy

RejectedBy

CompletedBy

where applicable.

---

Every status change must be traceable.

---

# Security Rules

Never trust:

UserId from frontend

Role from frontend

Balance from frontend

---

Always load:

Current User

Current Balance

from database.

---

# Notification Rules

Future Feature

Examples:

Withdrawal Created

Withdrawal Approved

Withdrawal Rejected

Withdrawal Completed

---

MVP:

Optional

---

